## Troubleshooting

### UI shows 502 Bad Gateway

```bash
kubectl get pods -n monitoring -o wide
# Check firewalld is disabled on workers
ansible workers -i hil-nodes.ini -b -m shell -a 'systemctl status firewalld'
# Test NodePort directly
curl -I http://10.45.10.172:30318/nagios/
```

### NRPE connection reset by peer

```bash
# Add pod CIDR to allowed_hosts on all nodes
ansible hil_cluster -i hil-nodes.ini -b -m shell -a \
  "sed -i 's/^allowed_hosts=.*/allowed_hosts=127.0.0.1,...,10.42.0.0\/16/' /etc/nagios/nrpe.cfg && systemctl restart nrpe"
```

### Config errors after pod restart

```bash
NAGIOS_POD=$(kubectl get pod -n monitoring -l app=nagios -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')
kubectl exec -n monitoring $NAGIOS_POD -- bash -c \
  'chown -R nagios:nagios /opt/nagios/var/ && chmod -R 775 /opt/nagios/var/ && chmod 777 /opt/nagios/var/rw/'
kubectl exec -n monitoring $NAGIOS_POD -- sv force-restart nagios
kubectl exec -n monitoring $NAGIOS_POD -- sv restart apache
```

### Validate config

```bash
kubectl exec -n monitoring $NAGIOS_POD -- nagios -v /opt/nagios/etc/nagios.cfg
```

### Reload Nagios

```bash
kubectl exec -n monitoring $NAGIOS_POD -- kill -HUP $(pgrep nagios)
```

### Watchdog CRITICAL (pipeline down)

```bash
# Check Alertmanager is running
kubectl get pods -n cattle-monitoring-system | grep alertmanager
# Check webhook is receiving
WEBHOOK_POD=$(kubectl get pod -n monitoring -l app=nagios-webhook -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')
kubectl logs -n monitoring $WEBHOOK_POD --tail=20
# Check Alertmanager alerts
curl -s http://10.43.218.173:9093/api/v2/alerts | python3 -m json.tool | grep alertname
```

### Manually submit passive check result

```bash
NAGIOS_POD=$(kubectl get pod -n monitoring -l app=nagios -o jsonpath='{.items[0].metadata.name}')
kubectl exec -n monitoring $NAGIOS_POD -- bash -c \
  "echo '[$(date +%s)] PROCESS_SERVICE_CHECK_RESULT;hil-rke2-cluster;<SERVICE>;0;OK - Manual clear' > /opt/nagios/var/rw/nagios.cmd"
```

### Initialize all passive checks to OK

```bash
kubectl exec -it -n monitoring $NAGIOS_POD -- bash
TIMESTAMP=$(date +%s)
SERVICES="Watchdog KubeAPIServerDown etcdInsufficientMembers KubeControllerManagerDown KubeSchedulerDown KubeNodeNotReady KubeNodeDiskPressure KubeNodeMemoryPressure KubeNodePIDPressure KubePodCrashLooping KubeDeploymentReplicasMismatch KubePersistentVolumeFillingUp KubeCPUOvercommit KubeMemoryOvercommit KubePodNotReady KubeContainerWaiting KubeDeploymentRolloutStuck CoreDNSDown KubeProxyDown KubePersistentVolumeErrors KubeJobFailed KubeStatefulSetReplicasMismatch"
for SVC in $SERVICES; do
  echo "[$TIMESTAMP] PROCESS_SERVICE_CHECK_RESULT;hil-rke2-cluster;$SVC;0;OK - Initialized" > /opt/nagios/var/rw/nagios.cmd
  sleep 0.5
done
```

